1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel graph convolutional network (GCN) framework for fault location in power distribution networks. The approach integrates multiple measurements and takes system topology into account. The paper also compares the proposed approach with other widely-used machine learning schemes. 
2. cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper deals with fault location in power distribution systems, which is a problem in systems and control. The proposed approach takes system topology into account and integrates multiple measurements to locate faults.

4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel graph convolutional network (GCN) framework for fault location in power distribution networks. The approach integrates multiple measurements and takes system topology into account. The paper also compares the proposed approach with other widely-used machine learning schemes.
